docs.abstract: New research shows diets rich in fruits and vegetables and low in starchy carbs can lower risk for age-related eye problems.
docs.lead_paragraph: Eating a diet rich in leafy vegetables, nuts and fish and low in starchy carbohydrates appears to lower risk for age-related macular degeneration, the leading cause of severe vision loss in people over 50.
docs.snippet: New research shows diets rich in fruits and vegetables and low in starchy carbs can lower risk for age-related eye problems.

headline.main: Finance Official's Husband Was City's Highest-Paid Parking Judge

docs.abstract: Also in Morning Buzz: the plight of the mentally ill in detention centers; an effort to help people who hoard; and more headlines from papers in the region.
docs.lead_paragraph: The highest-paid parking judge in New York City in 2006 and 2007 is the husband of the first deputy commissioner for the Finance Department, the agency that hires the judges.

docs.abstract: Young girls appear to be maturing sooner than earlier generations, according to a 15-year study of Danish children.
docs.lead_paragraph: A 15-year study of young girls in Denmark found that the average age of breast development has fallen by a full year compared to girls studied in the early 1990s.
docs.snippet: Young girls appear to be maturing sooner than earlier generations, according to a 15-year study of Danish children.
